\"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 10764, \"end\": 10776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Namibian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Namibian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Namibian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Namibian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Get in-depth reporting and opinions for \\t\\t\\t\\tonlyN$85 a month.\", \"from\": 10816, \"to\": 10877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Invest in journalism, invest in democracy -Subscribe Now!\", \"from\": 10878, \"to\": 10935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A ninth gold drew her level with former Soviet-era artistic gymnast Larisa Latynina as the only women ever to collect that many titles.\", \"from\": 10939, \"to\": 11074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11007, \"end\": 11022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larisa Latynina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The greatest distance swimmer the sport has seen, she had already won the 1500m and earned silver in the 4x200m freestyle relay and bronze in the 400m freestyle in Paris.\", \"from\": 11076, \"to\": 11246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11240, \"end\": 11245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.6335639744484463e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No other woman swimmer has won gold at four different Olympics and Ledecky said that was the record that gave her particular satisfaction.\", \"from\": 11248, \"to\": 11386, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think four times one is the one that kind of means the most to me.\", \"from\": 11388, \"to\": 11457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt like I put a lot of pressure on myself but I am just really happy that I could get the job done,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 11458, \"to\": 11573, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Unreal'  Titmus, who beat Ledecky in the 400m freestyle, was full of admiration for the American's achievement.\", \"from\": 11575, \"to\": 11687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11585, \"end\": 11591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 11664, \"end\": 11672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999995215845282, \"rank\": 4.748041003488697e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She's been winning this race since I was 11 years old and I turn 24 next month.\", \"from\": 11689, \"to\": 11769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That is just remarkable.\", \"from\": 11770, \"to\": 11794, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's unreal,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 11795, \"to\": 11819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh led from Australian Kaylee McKeown after the backstroke before the USA's Alex Walsh grabbed the advantage at the last turn, following the breaststroke leg.\", \"from\": 11821, \"to\": 11985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11821, \"end\": 11829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.43868477122635e-15, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 11839, \"end\": 11849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9994557756966315, \"rank\": 0.0005436133727876812, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 11897, \"end\": 11900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7277349896184667, \"rank\": 0.3741265067531048, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 11903, \"end\": 11913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But McIntosh once again produced the killer final lap to grab a thrilling victory.\", \"from\": 11987, \"to\": 12069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11991, \"end\": 11999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.43868477122635e-15, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American Kate Douglass took silver while McKeown took the bronze after Walsh, who had finished third, was disqualified.\", \"from\": 12071, \"to\": 12190, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12071, \"end\": 12079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999995215845282, \"rank\": 4.748041003488697e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 12080, \"end\": 12093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh was able to enjoy another of her casual strolls around the pool, waving to her fans with a gold medal around her neck.\", \"from\": 12192, \"to\": 12319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12192, \"end\": 12200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.43868477122635e-15, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's pretty surreal.\", \"from\": 12321, \"to\": 12342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just so proud of myself of how I have been able to recover and manage the events because it is a lot,\\\" said the teenager.\", \"from\": 12343, \"to\": 12469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hungary's Kristof Milak claimed his country's second swimming gold of these Games with victory in the men's 100m butterfly.\", \"from\": 12471, \"to\": 12594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12471, \"end\": 12478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.999999457852629, \"rank\": 5.421469696259925e-07, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 12489, \"end\": 12494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\", \"score\": 0.9893719204351404, \"rank\": 0.010742216526487677, \"text\": \"Milak\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada's Josh Liendo took silver while his compatriot Ilya Kharun claimed bronze.\", \"from\": 12596, \"to\": 12677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12596, \"end\": 12602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.6782079160021176, \"rank\": 0.3809166145961895, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 12605, \"end\": 12609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\", \"score\": 0.9999983307730251, \"rank\": 1.579870781605723e-06, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the second time this week that the Hungarians have been celebrating at La Defense Arena after Hubert Kos took gold in the 200m backstroke.\", \"from\": 12679, \"to\": 12824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12721, \"end\": 12731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.99999999981992, \"rank\": 1.650248764278273e-10, \"text\": \"Hungarians\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 12787, \"end\": 12790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kos\", \"score\": 0.9999999999959073, \"rank\": 4.11168874635411e-12, \"text\": \"Kos\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Milak was a silver medallist in the same event in Tokyo and also took silver in the 200m fly behind Leon Marchand this week.\", \"from\": 12826, \"to\": 12950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12826, \"end\": 12831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\", \"score\": 0.9893719204351404, \"rank\": 0.010742216526487677, \"text\": \"Milak\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\"}, {\"begin\": 12876, \"end\": 12881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999979648362359, \"rank\": 2.035167905134776e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 12931, \"end\": 12939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999900637704, \"rank\": 9.933121420204935e-09, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He now has two career golds in the fly, adding to his 200m success three years ago.\", \"from\": 12952, \"to\": 13035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the mixed 4x100m medley relay, the USA took gold with a world record time to eclipse China and Australia.\", \"from\": 13037, \"to\": 13145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13050, \"end\": 13069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.936786702672078e-29, \"text\": \"4x100m medley relay\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 13075, \"end\": 13078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7277349896184667, \"rank\": 0.3741265067531048, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/re